BP, Kingfisher, Home Retail Group: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-07T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/bp-kingfisher-home-retail-group-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index fell 21.11 points, or 0.4 percent, to
6,002.92. The FTSE All-Share Index retreated 0.3 percent to
3,129.81, while Ireland’s ISEQ Index slumped 1.4 percent to
2,959.79.  BP Plc (BP/)  : Azerbaijan’s state oil producer Socar sold
$485 million of bonds to the national oil wealth fund to finance
the acquisition of a 1.6 percent stake in a BP-operated project
in the  Caspian Sea . BP’s shares dropped 1 percent to 455 pence.  Kingfisher Plc (KGF)   and  Home Retail Group Plc (HOME)  : Kingfisher’s B&Q home-improvement chain and Home Retail
Group’s Homebase stores are teaming up with the U.K. government
to insulate homes as lawmakers debate incentives to boost
energy-saving. Kingfisher’s stock fell 0.4 percent to 265.9
pence, while Homebase’s shares dropped 1.5 percent to 162.5
pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  